1
00:00:00,767 --> 00:00:03,633
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:08,200
Whoever did this to me
must really hate me deeply.

3
00:00:08,333 --> 00:00:11,200
I only know one person who has
intense hatred toward my mother.

4
00:00:11,333 --> 00:00:12,267
You're done, Aldrin.

5
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:14,533
You are officially relieved
of your position.

6
00:00:14,667 --> 00:00:15,667
Don't touch me!

7
00:00:15,800 --> 00:00:18,700
All of this is your fault,
Edward.

8
00:00:18,833 --> 00:00:21,633
I thought you were never
going to call me again.

9
00:00:21,767 --> 00:00:23,833
- [CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]
- I want to hear your plan

10
00:00:23,967 --> 00:00:25,500
so I can get back at Edward.

11
00:00:25,633 --> 00:00:26,833
Good morning!

12
00:00:26,967 --> 00:00:28,933
I just want to see the building
you're planning to construct.

13
00:00:29,067 --> 00:00:30,000
Actually,

14
00:00:30,133 --> 00:00:31,567
we're going to demolish
the entire building.

15
00:00:31,700 --> 00:00:34,367
If it's beyond repair, it needs
to be completely removed

16
00:00:34,533 --> 00:00:36,000
to make room for something new
and better.

17
00:00:36,133 --> 00:00:38,533
I think that's the perfect place
to carry out my plan.

18
00:00:38,667 --> 00:00:40,167
What is he doing?

19
00:00:40,300 --> 00:00:44,733
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

20
00:01:25,300 --> 00:01:26,567
[SOBBING]

21
00:01:26,700 --> 00:01:28,633
Mom, I'm sorry.

22
00:01:28,767 --> 00:01:30,767
We didn't know that what you
went through

23
00:01:30,900 --> 00:01:32,467
was that complicated
and painful.

24
00:01:34,100 --> 00:01:38,900
I'm so sorry you had to find out
this way.

25
00:01:40,033 --> 00:01:44,133
Greg and I hid the truth
about my past.

26
00:01:46,633 --> 00:01:49,500
I only recently told Edward

27
00:01:49,633 --> 00:01:53,667
about it and I was planning
to tell you too.

28
00:01:54,933 --> 00:01:57,233
Then this happened.

29
00:01:57,367 --> 00:01:59,033
Mom,

30
00:01:59,167 --> 00:02:01,633
no matter what your past is,

31
00:02:01,767 --> 00:02:04,633
it doesn't change how I feel
about you.

32
00:02:04,767 --> 00:02:06,667
I know you

33
00:02:06,800 --> 00:02:08,867
better than the stories
they tell.

34
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:12,033
So no matter how much
they try to destroy you,

35
00:02:13,067 --> 00:02:15,100
you still have my love

36
00:02:15,267 --> 00:02:16,100
and respect.

37
00:02:16,233 --> 00:02:18,633
- Thank you, my child.
- [SOBBING]

38
00:02:18,767 --> 00:02:23,767
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

39
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:38,000
<i> I should have done this...</i>

40
00:02:39,167 --> 00:02:40,967
<i> a very long time ago.</i>

41
00:02:41,100 --> 00:02:42,633
<i> I'm letting you go.</i>

42
00:02:44,267 --> 00:02:46,167
<i> Thea is all yours now.</i>

43
00:02:46,300 --> 00:02:48,867
<i>Because I have no plans to ever
get back together with her.</i>

44
00:02:51,600 --> 00:02:54,800
<i>All of this is your fault,
Edward.</i>

45
00:02:56,067 --> 00:02:58,067
But you know,

46
00:02:58,200 --> 00:03:02,267
whoever did this to me must
really hate me deeply

47
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:04,933
to post those

48
00:03:05,067 --> 00:03:09,033
photos online
for the whole world to see.

49
00:03:10,367 --> 00:03:13,167
I'm not that woman anymore.

50
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:18,100
I left that part of my life
behind a long time ago.

51
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:21,900
Why are they bringing it back?

52
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:25,467
Could

53
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:27,833
Thea be involved in this?

54
00:03:27,967 --> 00:03:29,933
I don't think it's Thea.

55
00:03:30,067 --> 00:03:31,933
She knows nothing
about Mom's history.

56
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:36,667
There's only one person I know
who has deep hatred

57
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:37,800
toward my mother.

58
00:03:40,433 --> 00:03:43,267
He's the one who planned to take
revenge on Mom.

59
00:03:44,333 --> 00:03:46,300
I'm certain he's behind this.

60
00:03:46,433 --> 00:03:50,867
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

61
00:04:02,233 --> 00:04:03,167
Oh?

62
00:04:03,300 --> 00:04:04,700
What is this?

63
00:04:04,833 --> 00:04:06,233
A family reunion?

64
00:04:06,367 --> 00:04:08,233
We need to talk to you,
Mr. Castelo.

65
00:04:09,233 --> 00:04:10,900
We asked the IT department
to trace

66
00:04:11,033 --> 00:04:14,167
who spread the smear campaign
against Mom.

67
00:04:14,300 --> 00:04:16,367
And we found out that one
of your people, Aldrin,

68
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:17,933
was responsible.

69
00:04:18,067 --> 00:04:21,433
And I don't see why any
of that is my problem.

70
00:04:21,567 --> 00:04:24,433
Wasn't it enough that you
exposed Regina

71
00:04:24,567 --> 00:04:26,233
about her love child?

72
00:04:26,367 --> 00:04:29,133
And you still had to do this?

73
00:04:30,733 --> 00:04:33,433
You're not just destroying
Regina, Aldrin.

74
00:04:33,567 --> 00:04:36,500
You're ruining
the company's reputation.

75
00:04:36,633 --> 00:04:37,667
You seem to have forgotten

76
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:40,533
that you're part of the company
being destroyed

77
00:04:40,667 --> 00:04:42,767
because of what you did.

78
00:04:42,900 --> 00:04:44,700
Because of your personal
vendetta,

79
00:04:44,833 --> 00:04:46,833
thousands of people who depend
on Torrecampo Realty

80
00:04:46,967 --> 00:04:49,967
are affected.

81
00:04:50,100 --> 00:04:53,667
You are responsible
for your own actions.

82
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:56,367
That's why I proposed
to the board that

83
00:04:57,500 --> 00:04:59,100
you be removed from the company.

84
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:02,200
And they have all agreed.

85
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:04,967
So as of today,

86
00:05:05,100 --> 00:05:08,367
you are relieved
of your position

87
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:11,267
and you are out
of Torrecampo Realty.

88
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:13,067
You can't do this to me.

89
00:05:14,100 --> 00:05:15,933
I have my rights.

90
00:05:16,067 --> 00:05:18,033
No, no.

91
00:05:18,167 --> 00:05:20,033
We already did.

92
00:05:20,167 --> 00:05:21,633
You're done, Aldrin.

93
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:25,967
I'll sue all of you!

94
00:05:26,100 --> 00:05:27,267
We will also file charges
against you

95
00:05:27,400 --> 00:05:29,733
for destroying our family.

96
00:05:29,867 --> 00:05:31,600
We'll see each other in court.

97
00:05:31,733 --> 00:05:34,933
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

98
00:05:41,333 --> 00:05:42,500
Don't touch me!

99
00:05:43,533 --> 00:05:45,300
You will all regret this!

100
00:05:46,333 --> 00:05:47,867
Your family will pay for this!

101
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:52,100
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

102
00:05:59,900 --> 00:06:01,000
[CLATTERS]

103
00:06:03,067 --> 00:06:05,567
- [CLATTERS]
- [GRUMBLES]

104
00:06:07,100 --> 00:06:08,167
What?

105
00:06:08,300 --> 00:06:09,367
Are you happy now?

106
00:06:10,867 --> 00:06:12,467
[WHIMPERING]

107
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:13,900
Are you satisfied

108
00:06:14,033 --> 00:06:16,667
because your mistress's family
scored a win against me?

109
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:18,167
[GRUMBLES]

110
00:06:21,267 --> 00:06:23,033
Let them enjoy it.

111
00:06:23,167 --> 00:06:25,100
They're only making me angrier.

112
00:06:25,233 --> 00:06:27,700
I'll do even more

113
00:06:27,833 --> 00:06:29,300
to bring them down.

114
00:06:32,200 --> 00:06:35,100
- [PHONE RINGING]
- [INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

115
00:06:39,033 --> 00:06:41,867
[WHIMPERING]

116
00:06:42,033 --> 00:06:43,733
Aldrin,

117
00:06:43,867 --> 00:06:45,267
it's me, Thea.

118
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:47,700
[WHIMPERING]

119
00:06:47,833 --> 00:06:48,933
Shut up!

120
00:06:55,467 --> 00:06:56,800
Yes, Thea?

121
00:06:58,533 --> 00:07:02,600
You said you would
help me get revenge on Edward.

122
00:07:03,633 --> 00:07:05,067
I'll handle you.

123
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:08,033
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

124
00:07:16,100 --> 00:07:19,033
Dad, maybe we should've just
eaten at home

125
00:07:19,167 --> 00:07:21,567
so you wouldn't have gotten
tired.

126
00:07:21,700 --> 00:07:24,100
I am perfectly fine, son.

127
00:07:25,533 --> 00:07:28,767
I asked you here
because we're celebrating.

128
00:07:31,633 --> 00:07:32,800
Celebrating what?

129
00:07:34,633 --> 00:07:35,900
Edward,

130
00:07:36,033 --> 00:07:38,367
we want you to come back
to the company.

131
00:07:40,433 --> 00:07:41,167
Huh?

132
00:07:42,267 --> 00:07:43,767
What?

133
00:07:43,900 --> 00:07:46,167
I recommended to the board
that you lead

134
00:07:46,300 --> 00:07:48,767
the Asian Business
Complex Project.

135
00:07:50,700 --> 00:07:51,833
Dad,

136
00:07:51,967 --> 00:07:53,967
it's been a while since
I worked at the company.

137
00:07:54,100 --> 00:07:55,033
So why me?

138
00:07:56,467 --> 00:07:58,500
You know, if this is your way

139
00:07:58,633 --> 00:08:00,433
of making me feel that I belong,

140
00:08:00,567 --> 00:08:01,867
it's not necessary.

141
00:08:03,667 --> 00:08:06,233
I don't want you to risk your
biggest project just for me...

142
00:08:07,267 --> 00:08:10,667
I'm just correcting the
biggest mistake I made, Edward.

143
00:08:14,467 --> 00:08:17,067
When I pushed you away,

144
00:08:17,200 --> 00:08:19,200
things started falling apart.

145
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,500
Not just in the company,

146
00:08:24,900 --> 00:08:26,667
but also in our family.

147
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:30,867
Now that our family is
healing with your return,

148
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:32,367
I think

149
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:35,633
you're what the company needs
to rise again.

150
00:08:36,833 --> 00:08:40,200
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

151
00:08:41,233 --> 00:08:42,533
Are you sure?

152
00:08:49,500 --> 00:08:51,767
You've already forgiven
me as your father.

153
00:08:53,267 --> 00:08:54,333
Now,

154
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:57,700
as your boss, I hope
you can forgive me too.

155
00:08:57,833 --> 00:08:59,333
So please,

156
00:08:59,467 --> 00:09:01,267
come back to the company.

157
00:09:01,400 --> 00:09:05,767
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

158
00:09:07,167 --> 00:09:08,633
I don't know what to say.

159
00:09:10,900 --> 00:09:12,100
Dad, thank you.

160
00:09:13,833 --> 00:09:14,867
Paolo,

161
00:09:16,333 --> 00:09:18,200
you don't know how much
this means to me.

162
00:09:19,267 --> 00:09:20,633
I promise you,

163
00:09:20,767 --> 00:09:22,267
I'll do my best and

164
00:09:22,400 --> 00:09:24,333
I won't waste this opportunity.

165
00:09:24,467 --> 00:09:28,000
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

166
00:09:33,867 --> 00:09:36,067
This is what it feels like to be
acknowledged.

167
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:37,633
[CHUCKLES]

168
00:09:39,767 --> 00:09:41,267
You deserve this

169
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:42,867
more than anyone else.

170
00:09:45,933 --> 00:09:47,767
- [CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]
- A toast?

171
00:09:47,900 --> 00:09:48,700
Coffee, Dad.

172
00:09:48,833 --> 00:09:49,867
[LAUGHS]

173
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:51,000
Coffee.

174
00:09:51,133 --> 00:09:52,200
Why not?

175
00:09:52,333 --> 00:09:55,267
- Cheers.
- [CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

176
00:09:57,667 --> 00:09:58,833
- It's good.
- It's bitter.

177
00:09:58,967 --> 00:10:01,467
[LAUGHTER]

178
00:10:01,633 --> 00:10:03,633
Here's the creamer and sugar.

179
00:10:03,767 --> 00:10:04,967
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

180
00:10:05,100 --> 00:10:07,067
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

181
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:13,200
[SIGHS]

182
00:10:14,900 --> 00:10:17,367
I thought you were never going
to call me.

183
00:10:18,967 --> 00:10:21,000
I changed my mind.

184
00:10:21,133 --> 00:10:24,733
I want to hear your plan
so I can get revenge on Edward.

185
00:10:25,767 --> 00:10:26,967
Scotch, please.

186
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:31,267
You made the right decision,
Thea.

187
00:10:32,867 --> 00:10:36,800
Don't let yourself be thrown
away by Edward.

188
00:10:36,967 --> 00:10:40,200
You ought to make him pay
for what he's done to you.

189
00:10:41,933 --> 00:10:43,633
And how am I supposed
to do that?

190
00:10:43,767 --> 00:10:46,033
If you want to get even
with him,

191
00:10:48,033 --> 00:10:50,000
get rid of Edward

192
00:10:51,033 --> 00:10:52,567
once and for all.

193
00:10:55,333 --> 00:10:59,233
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

194
00:11:03,900 --> 00:11:04,500
[EXHALES]

195
00:11:05,233 --> 00:11:07,600
Get rid of Edward?

196
00:11:08,900 --> 00:11:10,200
I may be a cheater

197
00:11:10,333 --> 00:11:12,800
but I'm not a murderer.

198
00:11:13,833 --> 00:11:15,967
I can't do what you're asking.

199
00:11:18,333 --> 00:11:19,667
You see,

200
00:11:19,800 --> 00:11:21,733
I know for a fact that you can.

201
00:11:23,767 --> 00:11:25,733
Marj's sibling,

202
00:11:25,867 --> 00:11:27,967
didn't you attempt
to have him killed

203
00:11:28,100 --> 00:11:29,967
to protect your secret
with Paolo?

204
00:11:31,267 --> 00:11:33,833
You don't place someone
else's life

205
00:11:33,967 --> 00:11:36,233
above your own interests.

206
00:11:36,367 --> 00:11:37,967
That's not true.

207
00:11:38,100 --> 00:11:39,467
It was an accident.

208
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:43,000
I can't do what you're saying,

209
00:11:43,900 --> 00:11:45,733
especially to Edward.

210
00:11:45,867 --> 00:11:47,733
He's still my spouse.

211
00:11:47,867 --> 00:11:49,533
He's still Ashley's father.

212
00:11:49,667 --> 00:11:52,533
Paolo is Ashley's father.

213
00:11:52,667 --> 00:11:55,067
And you just said it yourself.

214
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:57,600
Edward took everything away
from you.

215
00:11:59,133 --> 00:12:00,300
Look, Thea.

216
00:12:01,967 --> 00:12:03,633
You and I

217
00:12:03,767 --> 00:12:05,833
have a lot in common.

218
00:12:05,967 --> 00:12:09,933
I know exactly how you feel when
it comes to the Torrecampos.

219
00:12:11,067 --> 00:12:14,167
Because that's also what I once
went through.

220
00:12:15,700 --> 00:12:17,500
They took

221
00:12:17,633 --> 00:12:19,267
everything from me.

222
00:12:21,567 --> 00:12:24,200
So why don't we just
work together?

223
00:12:24,333 --> 00:12:28,100
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

224
00:12:37,933 --> 00:12:39,300
[CLEARS THROAT]

225
00:12:40,967 --> 00:12:42,267
Tell me what you see.

226
00:12:44,467 --> 00:12:45,633
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

227
00:12:45,767 --> 00:12:48,067
You're not even in those photos.

228
00:12:48,233 --> 00:12:50,367
Where they're happy as a family.

229
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:54,033
And doesn't it seem

230
00:12:54,167 --> 00:12:58,400
that Edward is having a great
time without you?

231
00:12:58,533 --> 00:13:00,300
After he took your home
from you?

232
00:13:00,433 --> 00:13:01,800
Your child?

233
00:13:01,933 --> 00:13:03,767
It's not even his, by the way.

234
00:13:05,200 --> 00:13:07,000
My point is, Thea,

235
00:13:08,300 --> 00:13:10,467
he already took everything,

236
00:13:10,600 --> 00:13:13,533
he left nothing for you.

237
00:13:13,667 --> 00:13:15,633
That explains

238
00:13:15,767 --> 00:13:19,400
why you should be angrier
than you're showing.

239
00:13:21,267 --> 00:13:22,700
But I wonder why.

240
00:13:23,967 --> 00:13:25,167
Why is that?

241
00:13:26,633 --> 00:13:27,700
You're right.

242
00:13:28,733 --> 00:13:30,500
My anger toward him runs deep.

243
00:13:31,533 --> 00:13:33,333
But I would never

244
00:13:33,467 --> 00:13:35,333
kill Edward.

245
00:13:38,500 --> 00:13:39,267
You're right.

246
00:13:39,400 --> 00:13:40,733
You're right, I'm sorry.

247
00:13:40,867 --> 00:13:42,200
What was I thinking?

248
00:13:42,333 --> 00:13:43,467
It was just an idea.

249
00:13:43,600 --> 00:13:44,800
A terrible idea.

250
00:13:50,233 --> 00:13:52,533
But just like you,

251
00:13:52,667 --> 00:13:54,167
I can't do that

252
00:13:55,333 --> 00:13:57,100
because I'm not a murderer.

253
00:14:01,133 --> 00:14:02,333
You know what?

254
00:14:02,467 --> 00:14:05,500
I think it was a mistake
to even meet with you.

255
00:14:09,767 --> 00:14:10,733
Goodbye.

256
00:14:10,867 --> 00:14:15,433
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

257
00:14:22,300 --> 00:14:25,367
I don't need your help, Thea.

258
00:14:25,500 --> 00:14:28,333
There are other ways to get rid
of the trash

259
00:14:28,500 --> 00:14:30,500
and the family you belong to.

260
00:14:40,433 --> 00:14:42,567
The white one.

261
00:14:42,700 --> 00:14:44,600
- This one?
- Yes, the white one.

262
00:14:44,733 --> 00:14:48,833
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

263
00:14:57,100 --> 00:14:58,767
Are you done
with your lunch meeting?

264
00:14:58,900 --> 00:15:00,133
Yes.

265
00:15:00,267 --> 00:15:01,500
It went very well.

266
00:15:01,667 --> 00:15:03,200
Edward agreed as well.

267
00:15:05,433 --> 00:15:06,400
You know what?

268
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:10,267
I'm just glad that after
everything,

269
00:15:10,400 --> 00:15:12,400
things are getting better
in our lives.

270
00:15:13,800 --> 00:15:16,267
Jasmine is now in remission.

271
00:15:16,400 --> 00:15:18,533
And Ashley is making progress
in therapy.

272
